[30;1m1064 | [0m[35mMany systems err by asking the user to enter a password, and then[0m

[30;1m27 | [0m[35mDSA_ is a widespread public-key signature algorithm. Its security is[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35mbased on the discrete logarithm problem (DLP_). Given a cyclic[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35mgroup, a generator *g*, and an element *h*, it is hard[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35mto find an integer *x* such that *g^x = h*. The problem is believed[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35mto be difficult, and it has been proved such (and therefore secure) for[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35mmore than 30 years.[0m

[30;1m42 | [0m[35m--------------------[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35mThe security of the ElGamal encryption scheme is based on the computational[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35mDiffie-Hellman problem (CDH_). Given a cyclic group, a generator *g*,[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35mand two integers *a* and *b*, it is difficult to find[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35mthe element *g^{ab}* when only *g^a* and *g^b* are known, and not *a* and *b*. [0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35mAs before, the group is the largest multiplicative sub-group of the integers[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mmodulo *p*, with *p* prime.[0m

[30;1m989 | [0m[35mfrequently insufficient, because if some of their output is known, it[0m
[30;1m990 | [0m[35mis frequently possible to derive the generator's future (or past)[0m

[30;1m139 | [0m[35mwith the ``update()`` method, and can ask for the hash value at[0m
[30;1m140 | [0m[35many time by calling the ``digest()`` or ``hexdigest()``[0m
[30;1m141 | [0m[35mmethods.  The ``new()`` function can also be passed an optional[0m
[30;1m142 | [0m[35mstring parameter that will be immediately hashed into the object's[0m
[30;1m143 | [0m[35mstate.[0m
